<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6E4FC86FCEB9A4D" blockId="10.[166,1225,809,1220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD748FC86FDAC9D2A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[375,582,809,835]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD748FC86FDAC9D2A" box="[375,582,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Nediphya padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD473FC86FD609D2D" box="[588,650,809,836]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is larger than its congeners (carapace length 1.35 
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD699FCE5FF579D0A" box="[166,189,842,867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="FA3CBBEEDE6FFF9AD6F5FCE6FEB39D0D" box="[202,345,841,868]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8956" metricValueMax="3.1242" metricValueMin="2.667" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" unit="in" value="1.14" valueMax="1.23" valueMin="1.05">1.05–1.23 in</quantity>
other species). In general appearance it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD5C2FCE5FB6F9D0A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[1021,1157,841,867]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD5C2FCE5FB6F9D0A" box="[1021,1157,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD2B4FCE6FB229D0D" box="[1163,1224,841,868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Both species have wide lateral bands on the carapace and lack white guanine spots on the abdomen. The two species can be distinguished from each other by difference in carapace pattern (dark bands starting from 
<collectionCode id="5BD58ECEDE6FFF9AD47DFC06FD999DAD" box="[578,627,937,964]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">PLE</collectionCode>
in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD4A2FC05FCF09DAA" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[669,794,937,963]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD4A2FC05FCF09DAA" box="[669,794,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD51CFC06FC899DAD" box="[803,867,937,964]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD553FC05FC699DAA" box="[876,899,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">vs</emphasis>
. bands present on thoracic part), leg spination (tibia I with 5 spines in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD491FC65FCC19D8A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[686,811,969,995]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD491FC65FCC19D8A" box="[686,811,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD50DFC66FC989D8D" box="[818,882,969,996]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD545FC65FC7B9D8A" box="[890,913,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">vs</emphasis>
. 3; metatarsus IV without spines in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD72CFC45FE679A6A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[275,397,1001,1027]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD72CFC45FE679A6A" box="[275,397,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD7ADFC46FE259A6D" box="[402,463,1001,1028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD7EAFC45FE069A6A" box="[469,492,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">vs</emphasis>
. 2), and shape of the epigynal median plate (3 times wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD73FFBA5FE919A4A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[256,379,1033,1059]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD73FFBA5FE919A4A" box="[256,379,1033,1059]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6FFF9AD7BEFBA6FE559A4D" box="[385,447,1033,1060]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD7F9FBA5FE0E9A4A" box="[454,484,1034,1059]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">vs.</emphasis>
almost as long as wide).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6E4FB86FB609AAD" blockId="10.[166,1225,809,1220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Female 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE6FFF9AD7C1FB86FD829A2D" box="[510,616,1065,1092]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">holotype</typeStatus>
. Total length 3.1, carapace 1.35 long, 0.99 wide. Carapace yellowish brown with wide brown lateral bands starting behind 
<collectionCode id="5BD58ECEDE6FFF9AD238FBE6FBD19A0D" box="[1031,1083,1097,1124]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">PLE</collectionCode>
. Chelicerae, maxillae, labium and sternum yellow. Chelicerae with 3 prolateral and 2 retrolateral teeth. Legs yellowish. Femora, tibiae, metatarsi grayish distally and medially; legs I and II darker than III and IV. Abdomen light brown with complicated pattern of spots and stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD699FB48FE689A94" blockId="10.[166,386,1255,1277]" box="[166,386,1255,1277]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Length of leg segments</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD710FAB8FB729B44" blockId="10.[195,1176,1303,1429]" box="[303,1176,1303,1325]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Femur Patella Tibia Metatarsus Tarsus Total</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6F3FA9EFB799B2E" blockId="10.[195,1176,1303,1429]" box="[204,1171,1329,1351]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">I 1.65 0.48 1.46 1.50 0.75 5.84</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6F8FAE4FB799B08" blockId="10.[195,1176,1303,1429]" box="[199,1171,1355,1377]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">II 1.32 0.45 1.11 1.16 0.60 4.64</paragraph>
